node.text:
We were all born to live, born to love. Millions of years perfecting the art of it, and yet still,
somehow, it comes so unnaturally to most of us. xx Atticus

video by @mattrainor

node.text: I'm so excited for the Atticus Book Club @patreon to grow & to connect with a special community of writers, readers & poetry fans 🖤 Go to the link in bio or patreon.com/atticuspoetry to join. Hope to see you on there. Xo

node.text: This video stole my heart! Children & young people living in conflict are using poetry to call for peace! I'm so proud to team up with @UNICEF to share these powerful, emotive poems. As the world battles #COVID19, peace in countries affected by conflict is more critical than ever. UNICEF’s Poems for Peace provides a platform for children and young people affected by conflict to express themselves and have their voices heard, often for the first time. I'm committing now and in the future to providing these young poets around the world a place to have their voices heard. We hear you guys and we love you! #ChildrenUnderAttack #PoemsForPeace #WorldPoetryDay

node.text:
Hemingway has always been a huge inspiration for me. He’s a major reason I began writing eight years ago. (Also, probably boxing and drinking). I first read “A Moveable Feast” while wandering around Paris, and my life was never the same. In honor of “Papa’s” birthday, we made some fun new items. All limited edition! And enjoy free shipping on the bestselling ‘TIME’ print for the next 72 hours. Link in bio. xx 
“If you are lucky enough to have lived in Paris as a young man, then wherever you go for the rest of your life, it stays with you, for Paris is a moveable feast.” Hemingway

✨ Lost Poet Giveaway ✨

I created Lost Poet wanting the perfect wine to bring sailing and stargazing. It’s friends, it’s adventure, and it’s staying up all night. It’s the poetry of our lives.

I’m giving away a 4-pack of Lost Poet (including both Rosé & Red) & a special gift from the @atticuspoetryshop 🖤

To enter:
1️⃣ Double-tap this post
2️⃣ Follow @lostpoetwine & @atticuspoetryshop
3️⃣ Tag a friend in the comments
You can enter as many times as you like (just be sure to tag a different friend each time!). Winner will be picked on Tuesday 7/20/21 at 8:59 pm EST. 

Profile must be public to enter. Must be 21+ to enter and a U.S. resident
